sAuthor: Alaoui, F. E. M.[Fatima E. M.]
Citation.sAbstract: This work reports new experimental density data (954 points) for binary mixtures of 1-heptanol + heptane  over the composition range (seven compositions; 0 6 1-heptanol mole fraction x 6 1), between  298.15 and 393.15 K, and for 23 pressures from 0.1 MPa up to 140 MPa. An Anton Paar vibrating tube  densimeter, calibrated with an uncertainty of +-0.7 kg   m 3 was used to perform these measurements.  The experimental density data were fitted with a Tait-like equation with low standard deviations. Excess  volumes have been calculated from the experimental data. In addition, the isobaric thermal expansivity  and the isothermal compressibility have been derived from the Tait-like equation, provided as supplementary  material.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid density of biofuel mixtures: 1-Heptanol + heptane system at pressures up to 140 MPa and temperatures from 298.15 K to 393.15 K
